<h3 id="serving-private-content-through-cloudfront">Serving private content through CloudFront</h3>
<ul>
  <li>To serve private content through CloudFront we use Origin Access Identity, signed URLs or signed cookies</li>
  <li><a href="http://docs.aws.amazon.com/AmazonCloudFront/latest/DeveloperGuide/private-content-task-list.html">Setup serving private content througt CloudFront</a></li>
  <li><a href="http://docs.aws.amazon.com/AmazonCloudFront/latest/DeveloperGuide/private-content-restricting-access-to-s3.html">http://docs.aws.amazon.com/AmazonCloudFront/latest/DeveloperGuide/private-content-restricting-access-to-s3.html</a></li>
  <li><a href="http://docs.aws.amazon.com/AmazonCloudFront/latest/DeveloperGuide/private-content-signed-cookies.html">How to use signed cookies</a></li>
  <li><a href="http://docs.aws.amazon.com/AmazonCloudFront/latest/DeveloperGuide/private-content-signed-urls.html">How to use singed URLs</a></li>
</ul>

<h3 id="browser-base-upload-using-http-post">Browser-base Upload using HTTP Post</h3>
<ul>
  <li>To upload file to S3 we can upload directly to S3 instead of using webserver, when use this method Web Client must have S3 Signature</li>
  <li><a href="http://docs.aws.amazon.com/AmazonS3/latest/API/sigv4-UsingHTTPPOST.html">How to implement browser-base upload</a></li>
</ul>
